The paper deals with the design of MAC and PHY layer protocols for M2M communication, which falls under the scope of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of compressive sensing for multi-user detection suggests that Signal Processing (cs.SI) could also be a relevant sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which could potentially place it under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
